    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, STANDARD - 5000, 9000 CONV. - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        STEERING WHEEL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0501102" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>STEERING WHEEL</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the horn button assembly by placing your fingers evenly under the lip of the horn
                    button edge and pull up.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the horn cable from the button assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the steering wheel nut - snap ring on nut.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the steering wheel with puller (ZTSE 4229) or similar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501102">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0501102" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0501102" filename="../figg05/G0501102.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Steering Wheel Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the retainer with the slip ring, remove the three (3) pan head screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501103">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0501103" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0501103" filename="../figg05/G0501103.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. Retainer Pan Head Screws</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. PAN HEAD SCREWS</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. HORN CABLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. NARROW SPOKE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the retainer with slip ring and the three (3) pan head screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the steering wheel and tighten the nut as specified in the
                    <hotlnk document="s05011_10.xml" xrefid="hl0501101">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl0501101"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    . Discard the old snap ring and use a new snap ring on the nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the horn cable to the horn button assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the horn button in the steering wheel and firmly press it into place.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
